MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

94-2101. State v. Herman.

Ashtabula County, No. 93-A-1825. Appellant has filed an untimely appeal from the court of appeals’ decision entered on August 15,1994. In that appellant has failed to perfect an appeal pursuant to S.Ct.Prac.R. II(2)(A)(1),

IT IS ORDERED by the court, sua sponte, that this ease be, and hereby is, dismissed for lack of jurisdiction.
